        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "B-6 For each point P in B, let Sp be the set of points with all coordinates equal to 1 which differ from P in exactly one coordinate. Since there are more than 20+1/n points in B, and each Sp has n elements, the cardinalities of the sets Sp add up to more than 2\"+1, which is to say, more than twice the total number of points. By the pigeonhole principle, there must be a point in three of the sets, say Sp, Se, SR. But then any two of P, Q, R differ in exactly two coordinates, so PQR is an equilateral triangle, as desired.",
